giment of Scotland, in [[Glasgow]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 2nd Battalion, Royal Regiment of Scotland)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whatdotheyknow.com/request/596571/response/1430033/attach/3/20190911%20FOI09576%20Lai%20Response%20Letter%20ArmySec.pdf?cookie_passthrough=1 |title=Field Army Restructuring Battalion movements |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=11 September 2019 |website=WhatDoTheyKnow |access-date=12 September 2019 |quote=2nd and 6th Battalions The Royal Regiment of Scotland have transferred to 4th Infantry Brigade from 51st Infantry Brigade}}</ref>\n\n==== 7th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters East ====\n* '''[[7th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters East]]''', in [[Cottesmore, Rutland|Cottesmore]]\n** [[1st Queen's Dragoon Guards]], in [[Robertson Barracks, Norfolk|Swanton Morley]] with [[Jackal (vehicle)|Jackal]] reconnaissance vehicles<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/government/news/the-welsh-cavalry-swap-scimitars-for-jungle-boots The Welsh Cavalry swap Scimitars for jungle boots (They are due to rerole to 'Light Cavalry' and move to Swanton Morley, in Norfolk as part of the Army 2020 restructuring exercise)]</ref>\n** [[Royal Yeomanry]], in [[London]] & the [[Midlands]] with [[Land Rover Wolf#Weapons Mount Installation Kit|Land Rover RWMIK]] and [[Jackal (vehicle)|Jackal]] reconnaissance vehicles (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Queen's Dragoon Guards)<ref>[https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/corps-regiments-and-units/royal-armoured-corps/royal-yeomanry/ The Royal Yeomanry]</ref>\n** 1st Battalion, [[Royal Anglian Regiment]], in [[Royal Artillery Barracks, Woolwich|Woolwich Barracks]], [[Woolwich]]\n** 2nd Battalion, Royal Anglian Regiment, in [[Kendrew Barracks]], [[Cottesmore, Rutland|Cottesmore]]\n** 3rd Battalion, Royal Anglian Regiment, in [[Bury St Edmunds]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 2nd Battalion, Royal Anglian Regiment)\n** 4th Battalion [[Princess of Wales's Royal Regiment|The Princess of Wales\u2019s Royal Regiment]], in [[Redhill, Surrey|Redhill]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st & 2nd Battalion, The Princess of Wales's Royal Regiment)\n** 1st Battalion, The Rifles, in [[Beachley Barracks|Chepstow]]<ref name=\"rgbw-association\" />{{dead link|date=July 2013}}\n** 6th Battalion, The Rifles, in [[Wyvern Barracks]], [[Exeter]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, The Rifles)<ref>[http://www.army.mod.uk/documents/general/20130703-SUMMARY_OF_ARMY_2020_RESERVE_STRUCTURE_AND_BASING.pdf Summary of Army 2020 Reserve Structure and Basing, page 24] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203193356/http://www.army.mod.uk/documents/general/20130703-SUMMARY_OF_ARMY_2020_RESERVE_STRUCTURE_AND_BASING.pdf |date=2013-12-03 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.army.mod.uk/documents/general/20130703-A2020_Update.pdf Army 2010 Update, page 9]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==== 11th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters South East ====\n* '''[[11th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters South East]]''', in [[Aldershot Garrison|Aldershot]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/formations-divisions-brigades/1st-united-kingdom-division/11th-infantry-brigade-and-headquarters-south-east/|title=11th Infantry Brigade and HQ South East - British Army}}</ref>\n** 1st Battalion, [[Coldstream Guards]] in [[Victoria Barracks, Windsor|Victoria Barracks]], [[Windsor, Berkshire|Windsor]]\n** 1st Battalion, [[Irish Guards]] in [[Cavalry Barracks, Hounslow|Cavalry Barracks]], [[Hounslow]]\n** 1st Battalion, [[Royal Irish Regiment (1992)|Royal Irish Regiment]] in [[Clive Barracks]], [[Shropshire]]\n** 2nd Battalion, Royal Irish Regiment in [[Thiepval Barracks]], [[Lisburn]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Royal Irish Regiment)\n** 3rd Battalion, [[Princess of Wales's Royal Regiment]] in [[Canterbury]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, [[Royal Anglian Regiment]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armytigers.com/battalions/3-pwrr|title=3 PWRR}}</ref>)\n\n====38th (Irish) Brigade====\n* '''[[38th (Irish) Brigade]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/formations-divisions-brigades/regional-command/38-irish-brigade/|title=38th (Irish) Brigade}}</ref>, in [[Thiepval Barracks]], [[Lisburn]]\n** [[152 (North Irish) Regiment RLC|152 (North Irish) Regiment]], [[Royal Logistic Corps]] in [[Palace Barracks]], [[Holywood]]\n** 253 (North Irish) Medical Regiment, [[Royal Army Medical Corps]] in [[Belfast]]\n** 204 (North Irish) Field Hospital, Royal Army Medical Corps in Belfast\n\n==== 51st Infantry Brigade and Headquarters Scotland ====\n* '''[[51st Infantry Brigade and Headquarters Scotland]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/formations-divisions-brigades/1st-united-kingdom-division/51st-infantry-brigade-and-headquarters-scotland/|title=51st Infantry Brigade and Headquarters Scotland - British Army}}</ref>, in [[Forthside Barracks]], [[Stirling]]\n** [[Royal Scots Dragoon Guards]], in [[Edinburgh Castle]], [[Edinburgh]] with [[Jackal (vehicle)|Jackal]] reconnaissance vehicles\n** [[Scottish and North Irish Yeomanry]], in [[Redford Barracks]], Edinburgh with [[Land Rover Wolf#Weapons Mount Installation Kit|Land Rover RWMIK]] reconnaissance vehicles (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with Royal Scots Dragoon Guards)\n** 2nd Battalion, [[Royal Regiment of Scotland]] ([[Royal Highland Fusiliers]]) in [[Glencorse Barracks]], [[Penicuik]]\n** 3rd Battalion, Royal Regiment of Scotland ([[Black Watch]]) in [[Fort George, Highland|Fort George]], [[Inverness]]\n** Balaklava Company, 5th Battalion, Royal Regiment of Scotland ([[Argyll and Sutherland Highlanders]]) in Redford Barracks, Edinburgh\n** 6th Battalion, Royal Regiment of Scotland ([[52nd Lowland Volunteers]]) in [[Walcheren Barracks]], [[Glasgow]] (Army Reserve)\n** 7th Battalion, Royal Regiment of Scotland ([[51st Highland Volunteers]]) in Queen's Barracks, Perth (Army Reserve)\n** 3rd Battalion, [[The Rifles]] in [[Dreghorn Barracks]], Edinburgh\n** [[105th Regiment Royal Artillery|105 (Scottish and Ulster) Regiment]], [[Royal Artillery]] in Edinburgh (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with [[3rd Regiment Royal Horse Artillery|3 Regiment Royal Horse Artillery]])\n** [[39 Engineer Regiment (United Kingdom)|39 Regiment]], [[Royal Engineers]] in [[Kinloss Barracks]], [[Kinloss]]\n** [[71 Engineer Regiment (United Kingdom)|71 Regiment]], Royal Engineers in [[Leuchars Station]], [[Fife]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 39 Engineer Regiment)\n** 2 Close Support Battalion, [[Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers]] in Leuchars Station, Fife\n** 106 Battalion, Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers in [[East Kilbride]] (Army Reserve)\n** [[32 (Scottish) Signal Regiment|32 (Scottish) Regiment]], [[Royal Corps of Signals]] in Glasgow (Army Reserve)\n** [[154 (Scottish) Regiment RLC|154 (Scottish) Regiment]], [[Royal Logistic Corps]] in [[Dunfermline]] (Army Reserve)\n** 225 (Scottish) Medical Regiment, [[Royal Army Medical Corps]] in [[Dundee]] (Army Reserve)\n** 205 (Scottish) Field Hospital, Royal Army Medical Corps in Glasgow (Army Reserve)\n** 5 Military Intelligence Battalion, [[Intelligence Corps (United Kingdom)|Intelligence Corps]] in Redford Barracks, Edinburgh\n\n====160th (Welsh) Brigade====\n* '''[[160th (Welsh) Brigade]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/formations-divisions-brigades/regional-command/hq-160th-welsh-brigade/|title=160th (Welsh) Brigade - British Army}}</ref>\n\n====102 Logistic Brigade====\n* ''''[[102nd Logistic Brigade|102 Logistic Brigade]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/formations-divisions-brigades/1st-united-kingdom-division/102nd-logistic-brigade/|title=102 Logistic Brigade - British Army}}</ref>, in [[Prince William of Gloucester Barracks]], [[Grantham]]\n** [[6 Regiment RLC|6 Regiment]], [[Royal Logistic Corps]] in [[Dishforth Airfield]], [[North Yorkshire]]\n** 7 Regiment, Royal Logistic Corps in [[Kendrew Barracks]], [[Cottesmore, Rutland|Cottesmore]]\n** [[150 Regiment RLC|150 Regiment]], Royal Logistic Corps in [[Londesborough Barracks]], [[Kingston upon Hull]] (Army Reserve)\n** [[158 Regiment RLC|158 Regiment]], Royal Logistic Corps in [[Peterborough]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 7 Regiment RLC)\n** [[159 Regiment RLC|159 Regiment]], Royal Logistic Corps in [[Coventry]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 6 Regiment RLC)\n** [[3 Medical Regiment (United Kingdom)|3 Medical Regiment]], [[Royal Army Medical Corps]] in [[Fulwood Barracks]], [[Preston, Lancashire|Preston]]\n** [[254th Medical Regiment|254 Medical Regiment]], Royal Army Medical Corps in [[Cambridge]] (Army Reserve)\n** 1 Close Support Battalion, [[Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers]] in Munster Barracks, [[Catterick Garrison]]\n\n{{Location map+ | United Kingdom\n| width = 330\n| caption = <center>British Army Reaction Forces locations</center>\n| relief = 1\n| places =\n  {{Location map~ | United Kingdom\n    | label = <small>[[Colchester|16 Air Assault]]</small>\n    | position = left\n    | background = white\n    | mark = Cyan pog.svg\n    | lat_deg = 51 | lat_min = 53 | lat_dir = N\n    | lon_deg = 00 | lon_min = 54 | lon_dir = E\n  }}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom\n    | label = <small>[[Bulford|'''3 (UK) Div.'''<br />12 Armoured<br />20 Armoured]]</small>\n    | position = bottom\n    | background = white\n    | mark = Green pog.svg\n    | lat_deg = 51 | lat_min = 13 | lat_dir = N\n    | lon_deg = 01 | lon_min = 46 | lon_dir = W\n  }}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom\n    | label = <small>[[Tidworth Camp|1 Armoured]]</small>\n    | position = top\n    | background = white\n    | mark = Green pog.svg\n    | lat_deg = 51 | lat_min = 14 | lat_dir = N\n    | lon_deg = 01 | lon_min = 40 | lon_dir = W\n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | United Kingdom\n    | label = <small>[[Aldershot Garrison|101 Logistic]]</small>\n    | position = right\n    | background = white\n    | mark = Purple pog.svg\n    | lat_deg = 51 | lat_min = 15 | lat_dir = N\n    | lon_deg = 0 | lon_min = 45 | lon_dir = W\n  }}\n}}\n\n=== 3rd (United Kingdom) Division ===\nDivision referred to as the \"Reaction Force\"\n* '''[[3rd Division (United Kingdom)|3rd (United Kingdom) Division]]''',<ref name=\"Army 2019\" /> in [[Bulford Camp|Bulford]] (Reaction Forces)\n** [[Royal Wessex Yeomanry]], in [[Bovington Camp|Bovington]] (Army Reserve \u2013 [[Challenger 2]] crew replacement for any of the tank regiments below)\n** Pre-Hospital Care Group (from [[2nd Medical Brigade (United Kingdom)|2 Medical Brigade]])<ref name=ZacchiFOI />\n\n==== 1st Armoured Infantry Brigade ====\n* ''' [[1st Armoured Infantry Brigade (United Kingdom)|1st Armoured Infantry Brigade]]''', in [[Tidworth Camp|Tidworth]] (to become 1st Strike Brigade in 2019).\n** [[Royal Tank Regiment]], in Tidworth with Challenger 2 [[main battle tanks]] (to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"RTR19\">{{cite web|url=http://www.royaltankregiment.com/Uploads/Files/en-GB/20170317-RTR%20ERE%20SPRING%2017%20UPDATE-O.PDF|title=RTR ERE SPRING 17 UPDATE|publisher=Royal Tank Regiment Association|accessdate=31 May 2017}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n** 1st Battalion, [[Mercian Regiment]], in Bulford with [[Warrior tracked armoured vehicle|Warrior]] tracked [[infantry fighting vehicles]] (to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)\n** 4th Battalion, Mercian Regiment, in [[Wolverhampton]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Mercian Regiment, to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)\n** 1st Battalion, [[Royal Regiment of Fusiliers]], in Tidworth with Warrior tracked infantry fighting vehicles (to transfer to 20th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"Fusiliers' Website\">{{cite web|url=http://thefusiliers.org/the-colonels-christmas-message-and-news-of-regimental-growth/|title=News of Regimental growth, in the Colonel'