 17 UPDATE|publisher=Royal Tank Regiment Association|accessdate=31 May 2017}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n** 1st Battalion, [[Mercian Regiment]], in Bulford with [[Warrior tracked armoured vehicle|Warrior]] tracked [[infantry fighting vehicles]] (to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)\n** 4th Battalion, Mercian Regiment, in [[Wolverhampton]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Mercian Regiment, to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)\n** 1st Battalion, [[Royal Regiment of Fusiliers]], in Tidworth with Warrior tracked infantry fighting vehicles (to transfer to 20th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"Fusiliers' Website\">{{cite web|url=http://thefusiliers.org/the-colonels-christmas-message-and-news-of-regimental-growth/|title=News of Regimental growth, in the Colonel's Christmas Message|work=Fusiliers' Website|accessdate=22 December 2016}}</ref>\n** 5th Battalion, Royal Regiment of Fusiliers, in [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Royal Regiment of Fusiliers, to transfer to 20th Armoured Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"Fusiliers' Website\" />\n\n[[File:3rd (UK) Division 2018.png|thumb|right|upright=1.5|Structure of 3rd (UK) Division under Army 2020 Refine]]\n\n==== 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade ====\n* '''[[12th Armoured Infantry Brigade (United Kingdom)|12th Armoured Infantry Brigade]]''', in [[Bulford]]\n** [[Royal Lancers]], in [[Catterick Garrison|Catterick]] with [[FV107 Scimitar]] reconnaissance vehicles (to be equipped from 2017 with [[Ajax (Scout SV)|Ajax]], become an armoured cavalry regiment, transfer to the Strike Experimentation Group and move to Warminster)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://delhispearman.org.uk/notice-of-regimental-amalgamation-5thjuly-2012/|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130505152240/http://delhispearman.org.uk/notice-of-regimental-amalgamation-5thjuly-2012/|url-status=dead|archive-date=5 May 2013|title=9th/12th Charitable Association Website|publisher=Delhispearman.org.uk|date=5 July 2012|accessdate=2013-03-13}}</ref>\n** 1st Battalion, [[Yorkshire Regiment]], in [[Battlesbury Barracks|Warminster]] with [[Warrior tracked armoured vehicle|Warrior]] tracked [[infantry fighting vehicles]] (to be equipped with [[Mechanised Infantry Vehicle]], transfer to 1st Strike Brigade and move to Catterick in 2020)\n** 1st Battalion, [[Royal Welsh]], in Tidworth with Warrior tracked infantry fighting vehicles<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://rwf-forum.co.uk/vBulletin/showthread.php?17113-Regimental-Update|title=Regimental Update|publisher=Rwf-forum.co.uk|date=11 February 2013|accessdate=2013-03-13}}</ref>\n** 3rd Battalion, [[Royal Welsh]], in [[Cardiff]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Royal Welsh<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.army.mod.uk/infantry/regiments/25384.aspx|title=3 Royal Welsh|accessdate=4 November 2014}}</ref>)\n\n==== 20th Armoured Infantry Brigade ====\n* '''[[20th Armoured Infantry Brigade (United Kingdom)|20th Armoured Infantry Brigade]]''', in Bulford\n** [[Royal Dragoon Guards]], in Catterick with [[FV107 Scimitar]] reconnaissance vehicles (to be equipped from 2017 with [[Ajax (Scout SV)|Ajax]], become a mechanized regiment, transfer to the Strike Experimentation Group and move to Warminster)\n** [[Queen's Royal Hussars]], in [[Athlone Barracks|Sennelager]], (Germany) with [[Challenger 2]] [[main battle tanks]] (to move to Tidworth)\n** 5th Battalion, [[The Rifles]], in Bulford with Warrior tracked infantry fighting vehicles<ref name=\"rgbw-association\" />{{dead link|date=July 2013}} (to be paired with 7th Battalion, The Rifles)\n** 7th Battalion, The Rifles, in [[Reading, Berkshire|Reading]] (Army Reserve<ref name=\"autogenerated9\"/> \u2013 paired with 5th Battalion, The Rifles)\n\n==== Strike Experimentation Group ====\n* '''[[Strike Experimentation Group (United Kingdom)|Strike Experimentation Group]]''', in [[Warminster]]\n** [[